{
  "text": "The extension of this Laplacian-based model for stationary (isotropic) Gaussian random fields to non-stationary ones relies on the notion of Riemannian manifold [CITATION_1] . A Riemannian manifold is the association of a manifold with a Riemannian metric. On one hand, the manifold is a set that can locally be considered as Euclidean. On the other hand, the Riemannian metric is an application that smoothly associates to each point x of the manifold an inner product that redefines the notions of length and of angles for infinitely small vectors that would be attached to x.",
